Paper: hep-th/9302087

Date: 1993-02-19

Title: On the Uniqueness of the Newton-Wigner Position Operator

Authors: Dan Radu Grigore

Comments: 10 pages, PLAIN-TEX

Journal-ref: Int.J.Theor.Phys. 32 (1993) 555-564

It is shown that the quantum position operator of Newton and Wigner fornon-zero mass systems is uniquely determined if one imposes a quantum''manifest covariance'' condition of the same type as the similar condition ofCurrie, Jordan and Sudarshan in the the framework of the Hamiltonian formalism.